<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title></title></head><body><div><h2 style="margin:2pt 0pt; page-break-after:avoid"><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">Belgian House of Representatives</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">—</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence</span></h2><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">House of Lords inquiry – Draft replies</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Youth unemployment in one country has a negative impact for the whole </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">union :</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> it threatens social cohesion, internal demand (including demand for products of other Member States), potential growth, political and economic …  Therefore, EU action is needed and warranted.  Such action, e.g. through the country specific recommendations (CSRs) or through the Youth Employment Guarantee (YEG) recommendation fall entirely within the scope of the Treaty and are clearly additional to Member States’ own initiatives.  Moreover, Member States maintain their full autonomy in shaping the policy measures to implement them.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">EU added value comes through the establishment of common benchmarks, peer pressure, policy exchange (mutual learning) and through the provision of funds for those Member States and regions where youth unemployment is highest.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The YEI allows Member States to diversify their efforts.  The YEI establishes a benchmark (an offer within four months of becoming NEET), but allows Member States to put in place the most suitable measures for specific groups.  It does not define policies for each group separately, since this would not respect Member States’ autonomy. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">On the macro level, the evaluation in the framework of the European Semester, i.a. through the multilateral surveillance by the Employment Committee, seems to function rather well. Evaluation on the micro level within the ESF is a regional competence.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">This is a (exclusive) regional competence in Belgium.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The Youth Forum is often involved in discussions, though not in a formal way.  However, the social partners (in this case the trade unions) are involved in the EU decision making process, and they (should) also represent young people.  Belgium wants to reinforce social </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">partners</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> involvement in the processes – and would suggest that they take their responsibility along with the Youth Forum.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Mobility, in particular for young people, should be encouraged.  Studying and working in another country is an enriching experience and helps the functioning of the EU labour market as a whole.  Negative consequences (brain drain, unfair competition…) should be tackled through appropriate measures.  The structural funds should encourage economic development of regions lagging behind.  Legislation such as the posting directive and the further development of policy benchmarks in the field of e.g. the minimum wage is needed to avoid unfair competition.  </span></li><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The exchange of best practices among the Public Employment Services through their network can foster the development of new approaches.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">8 October 2013</span></p></div></body></html>